Buffalo Gulf Coast Terminals, a
provider of oil storage services, is seeking a $275 million term
loan to help finance its purchase of Houston Fuel Oil Terminal
Co. from ArcLight Capital Partners LLC, according to a person
with knowledge of the transaction.  Barclays Bank Plc is arranging the deal for the Alinda
Capital Partners LLC-owned company, said the person, who
declined to be identified because the terms are private. The
bank will host a lender meeting on Sept. 8 in  New York .  Chris Beale, a partner at Greenwich, Connecticut-based
